    • Method Detail

      • setFields

        public void setFields(Object o,
             Yggdrasil y)
               throws StreamCorruptedException
        Sets all fields of the given Object to the values stored in this Fields object.

        This also sets transient fields.

        Parameters:
        o - The object whose fields should be set
        y - A reference to the Yggdrasil object used for loading - this is required for incompatible or missing fields. You can use null if your class implements YggdrasilSerializable.YggdrasilRobustSerializable and handles all fields, or if you are sure that fields only contains existing fields. A NullPointerException may be thrown otherwise.
        Throws:
        StreamCorruptedException
